race.comment: AMERICAN ESCAPE (6) stuck on well over 1200m last time out and now rises to 1400m for the first time which looks ideal. The inside draw should see her get every chance in the run and Brad Parnham hops on board having won aboard her previously. Ticks plenty of boxes today. DESERT DANCING (7) flew home first-up over 1200m, beating home AMERICAN ESCAPE on that occasion. She's been back to the trials since and she's a two-time winner second-up. Rawiller rides and while she's likely to get back in the run, she'll be storming home late in the race. AUTO CRUISE (9) has been left with too much to do in both runs back this time, but now third-up and at her peak, she should be able to take closer order under CJP. She's a progressive type knocking on the door, and with further improvement likely she'll be hard to hold out. BARTIME (1) led and won here last time out beating AUTO CRUISE and has to be included despite the wide gate. GOLD MAKER (2) is racing well and is not to be discounted.
